##Key Insights
User acquisition is growing rapidly, but active users remain stable, indicating retention challenges.
Early-stage retention is low (~15–25%), highlighting weak user activation post-signup.
Retention patterns are non-linear, with users returning after inactivity → indicating sporadic (non-habitual) usage behavior.
Engagement metrics are similar for churned and retained users, suggesting retention depends on value perception, not just usage volume.
Feature usage is distributed across all features, with no clear “sticky” feature driving retention.
Beta features show slightly higher engagement, indicating potential opportunities for experimentation.
Retention is consistent across plan tiers, suggesting pricing is not the primary churn driver.
Trial users convert effectively, but sustaining long-term engagement remains a challenge.
